dataIdInfo.idPurp:
This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data.
[this parcel map exists to provide a representation of the shape and location of assessment and title parcels. They were created to support the taxation and assessment base for the Real Property Listing division of the Land Records Department. The maps also provide a base for land information activities used by the County government agencies such as zoning, building, sanitation, planning, conservation, and transportation departments et cetera. Other uses include information used by the private property owners and real estate and title professionals.]
dataIdInfo.idAbs: This data layer represents parcels for Sawyer County, Wisconsin in 2014. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, Sawyer_Parcels_2014.gdb. [The areas of land that are managed for the real estate tax system, these may be multipart polygons, all have a unique tax key number.]
